<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Class Terms and Conditions</title>
    <style>
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6; color: #000; padding: 60px 80px; background: white; }
        .header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom: 3px solid #000; padding-bottom: 20px; }
        .document-title { font-size: 24pt; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 15px; text-transform: uppercase; }
        .date { text-align: right; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 20px; color: #555; }
        .info-box { background: #f8f8f8; border: 2px solid #333; padding: 25px; margin: 30px 0; border-radius: 5px; }
        .info-box h3 { margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 14px; text-transform: uppercase; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding-bottom: 5px; }
        .info-row { display: flex; margin-bottom: 8px; }
        .info-label { font-weight: bold; width: 200px; flex-shrink: 0; }
        .info-value { flex: 1; }
        .section { margin: 25px 0; }
        .section-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; }
        .section-content { text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 10px; }
        ul { margin-left: 40px; margin-bottom: 15px; }
        li { margin-bottom: 5px; }
        strong { font-weight: bold; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header"><div class="document-title">CLASS TERMS AND CONDITIONS</div></div>
    <div class="date">Last Updated: {{date}}</div>
    <div class="info-box">
        <h3>Business Information</h3>
        <div class="info-row"><div class="info-label">Business Name:</div><div class="info-value">{{BusinessName}}</div></div>
        <div class="info-row"><div class="info-label">Email:</div><div class="info-value">{{Email}}</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">1. CLASS REGISTRATION</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Classes must be booked in advance. Registration is confirmed upon payment or use of class credit. We reserve the right to cancel classes due to low enrollment or unforeseen circumstances.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">2. PAYMENT AND PRICING</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Class prices are subject to change. Payment is required at the time of booking. Class packages expire after the specified period and are non-refundable.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">3. CANCELLATION POLICY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Cancel at least 12 hours before class start time to receive credit. Late cancellations and no-shows will result in forfeiture of class credit or payment.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">4. CLASS CONDUCT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Follow all instructor directions, use equipment properly, and respect fellow participants. Disruptive behavior may result in removal from class without refund.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">5. HEALTH AND SAFETY</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            Participation is at your own risk. You must disclose any medical conditions or injuries to instructors. <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong> is not liable for injuries sustained during classes.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">6. SUBSTITUTIONS AND MODIFICATIONS</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            We may substitute instructors or modify class content without notice. If we cancel a class, you will receive credit or refund.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title">ACKNOWLEDGEMENT</div>
        <div class="section-content">
            By attending classes at <strong>{{BusinessName}}</strong>, you agree to these terms and conditions.
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>